data: Georgia Chamberlain and her best friend Jo -- having just moved to New York City from Atlanta -- work together at the perfume counter at an upscale department store in the city. Georgia is desperate to leave her shift early in order to audition for the lead in a revival of the musical Damn Yankees. Always one to help a friend, Jo fakes a medical emergency as their way out of their work shift. While at the casting office, Georgia sings a phenomenal rendition of "Lola," but the casting director (Trent) informs Georgia she can never pass as a seductress due to her size. After a pep talk from her eccentric Aunt Honey, Georgia appears at Trent's apartment with an irresistible basket of food -- and proves to him that she is every bit the seductress. Later, back at work, Jo has a run-in with her professor, who happens to be making a return at the store. With a push from Georgia, Jo works up the nerve to ask the professor for a second interview for the Physics graduate program.

Georgia’s new man, Brian, is perfect in every way – almost too perfect. Georgia begs Jo to find Brian on Facebook, convinced the social networking site will reveal at least some of his flaws. Unable to learn anything, Georgia begins to wonder if she finally found the guy of her dreams. Meanwhile, Aunt Honey believes that Jo’s math student, Mikey, is madly in love with Jo. When Mikey schedules a tutoring session for Saturday night, Jo is convinced that Aunt Honey was right. Although the evening doesn’t go quite as planned, Jo realizes that Mikey’s computer skills might come in handy in helping her investigate Brian. Abandoning all thoughts of tutoring, Jo and Mikey team up to learn the true identity of Georgia’s mysterious man.

data: [Katie's_Law|Katie Sepich Enhanced DNA Collection Act of 2012]

Directs the Attorney General to make grants to assist states with costs associated with the implementation of minimum or enhanced DNA collection processes. Defines such processes for the purpose of this Act.

Amends the federal criminal code to eliminate certain limitations on the length of Secret Service protection for former Presidents and their spouses and children. Authorizes the Secret Service to protect: (1) former Presidents and their spouses for their lifetimes, except that protection of a spouse shall terminate in the event of remarriage; and (2) children of a former President who are under age 16.
Video Privacy Protection Act Amendments Act of 2012

Amends provisions of the federal criminal code authorizing a video tape service provider to disclose personally identifiable information concerning any consumer to any person with the informed, written consent of the consumer to: (1) allow such consent to be provided through an electronic means using the Internet; (2) require such consent be in a form distinct and separate from any form setting forth other legal or financial obligations of the consumer; (3) allow such consent to be given in advance for a set period of time, not to exceed two years or until consent is withdrawn by the consumer, whichever is sooner; and (4) require the video tape service provider to provide an opportunity for the consumer to withdraw such consent on a case-by-case basis or to withdraw from ongoing disclosures, at the consumer's election.

Foreign and Economic Espionage Penalty Enhancement Act of 2012

Amends the federal criminal code to increase the maximum fine for economic espionage (i.e., stealing or obtaining, duplicating or conveying, or buying or possessing trade secrets without authorization, intending or knowing that the offense will benefit any foreign government, foreign instrumentality, or foreign agent) committed by individuals (from $500,000 to $5 million) or by organizations (from $10 million to $10 million or 3 times the value of the stolen trade secret to the organization).

UST Tan Yan Kee Student Center

The massive edifice named after the patron saint of the University is a semi-centralized system for the productive exchange of ideas among researchers in the fields of arts, humanities, science, technology, social sciences, and education. It also houses the UST Graduate School.
The four-story edifice, in commemoration of Miguel de Benavides' 400th death anniversary, is the first one-stop cancer therapy center in the Philippines which was inaugurated on August 21, 2006.
The UST Health Service serves as the University clinic. It provides primary health care to students, employees, and administrators.

The UST Hospital was formally opened its charity unit on February 15, 1945, in a building which stood at the rear of the Main Building. The building house classrooms for the medical school and became the site of the first charity hospital.

On March 7, 1946, the charity hospital was opened together with UST Hospital, occupying the first floor. The whole charity ward was transferred and eventually renamed the USTH-Clinical Division when it was completed in 1965 and formally inaugurated on March 6, 1966.

data: The Son of Heaven sits on a golden throne.
The god of the road riding on a dappled horse bestows his favour on two travellers.
An eagle with golden wings catches and eats whatever it wants.
A white-spotted falcon perches in a sandalwood tree.
A bear and a boar fight together, and are both injured.
A man arrives with good news.
A leopard yawns in the reeds.
Messengers on a yellow horse and a dark brown horse bring good news.
An abandoned old woman stays alive by licking a greasy spoon.
A raven is tied to a tree.
Chicks, fawns and children lost in the fog are found safe after three years.
A horse that is lost in the desert finds grass to eat and water to drink.
A tent is in good condition.
An old hoopoe sings at the new year.
A woman drops her mirror in a lake.
A boy finds some eagle droppings.
A blind foal tries to suckle at a stallion.
A yoke of oxen harnessed to a plough cannot move.
The sun rises and shines on the world.
A sheep encounters a wolf but remains safe.
A poor man's son returns home after earning some money.
A tiger returns to its den after finding some prey.
Some felt falls into the water.
A khan returns victorious from battle.
A man returning from war encounters a swan who leads him home.
A man has no titles and a bad reputation.
An old ox is bitten by ants.
Heaven decrees that a slave girl becomes a queen.
A roan horse is fettered and cannot move.
A stout-hearted young man shoots an arrow that splits a rock.
A white-spotted cow gives birth to a white-spotted male calf.
A woman who has left her cups and bowls behind returns and finds them where she left them.
A falcon hunting water birds encounters an eagle.
A hawk pounces on a rabbit, but it injures its claws and the rabbit escapes.
A fawn is without grass and water.
A camel is stuck in a marsh, and is eaten by a fox.
A man encounters a god who wishes him plentiful livestock and long life.
The old god of the road who mends things brings order to the country.
A tiger encounters a wild goat, but the goat escapes down a cliff.
A roan horse and a bay horse are made to run until they are exhausted.
An eagle summers on a green rock, and winters on a red rock.
When a man is depressed and the sky is cloudy the sun comes out.
It rains and the grass grows.
A slave speaks to his master; a raven speaks to heaven.
A man goes to war, and makes a name for himself.
A stallion summers beneath the nut trees, and winters beneath the trees where the birds roost.
A girl's lover has died, and the water in her pail has frozen.
painful to start with, and good later

A crane lands but is caught in a snare.
A yargun (?) deer climbs the mountains during the summer.
The khan went hunting and caught a roe buck.
A grey falcon with a white neck sits on a rock, and summers in a poplar tree.
A fat horse has a hard mouth that will not heal.
